American Science & Engineering Inc. Key Developments

American Science & Engineering Inc. Wins a $20,965,958 Federal Contract
Jul 1 17
American Science & Engineering Inc. won a $20,965,958 federal contract from the U.S. Army Contracting Command for the sustainment of Iraqi-owned Z-Backscatter vans with low-energy, non-intrusive inspection equipment screening systems. The place of performance will be in Billerica, Massachusetts.


American Science & Engineering Inc. Wins $15.73 Million Federal Contract
Apr 4 17
American Science & Engineering Inc., Billerica, Massachusetts, won $15,730,714 sole source federal contract from the U.S. Department of State for the supply of high intensity scanners for Suez Canal, Egypt.


American Science & Engineering Inc. Wins Indefinite Delivery, Indefinite Quantity Contract from U.S. Customs and Border Protection for Z Portal® Cargo and Vehicle Screening Systems
Oct 24 16
OSI Systems Inc. announced that its recently acquired business, American Science and Engineering Inc. has been awarded an indefinite delivery, indefinite quantity (IDIQ) contract from U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) for Z Portal® cargo and vehicle screening systems. The two-year Z Portal sole-source IDIQ contract is valued up to $64 million. AS&E also received the first delivery order under the IDIQ contract valued at approximately $35 million. The Z Portal systems are expected to be deployed for homeland security applications at multiple border locations. The Z Portal system is the only drive-through cargo and vehicle inspection system that uses multiple detection technologies to provide up to six views of the vehicle under inspection. The Z Portal system incorporates AS&E’s latest source and detector innovations in a more compact design, enabling improved image quality at higher throughput rates in space-constrained locations such as checkpoints at congested border crossings.


